The CA state gov exists for one reason and one reason only: max revenue
generation to support itself. The fact that the vehicle was not operated
will be totally irrelevant to them; if it wasn't filed as non-op each year,
they will insist on full back registration. I would register out of state if
possible. You could then re-register in CA after a few months.

Rick
'77 Westy "Pumpkin II"
Stock 2.0 L FI

